Class InvalidCharException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • InvalidCharException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    public class InvalidCharException
extends java.lang.Exception
    InvalidCharException is a subclass of the Exception class with the task of handling errors relating to invalid ASCII Characters outside of the range 42-122.
    See Also:
